We will now calculate the average accounting receivables by using the formula in Step 3. But first, we need to find the **daily sales.**

Since the weekly sales are known, the daily sales can be determined by dividing the weekly sales by $7$. Accordingly,

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Daily Sales}&=\frac{\$21,900}{7}
\end{aligned}$$

Thus, we have the Daily sales as $\$\dfrac{21,900}{7}$.
